The scheme will come into effect from 1 April 2018 and will apply to all Council Tax liabilities for the financial year 2018/19. The Council Tax Reduction Scheme sets out how much reduction in Council Tax liability will be awarded to those on low incomes. The amount of reduction awarded is based on the Council’s assessment of a person’s financial circumstances and their entitlement to certain benefits. The Council has also approved a Council Tax Reduction Scheme Hardship Fund for 2018/19. This fund will provide additional help to those in financial hardship who are facing exceptional and unavoidable expenses which cannot be deferred. For further information on the Council Tax Reduction Scheme and Hardship Fund, please visit www.rother.gov.uk/counciltaxreduction or contact the Benefits Team on 01424 787000.
